******
[2] Indonesia (Bali)
Date: Wed 14 May 2008
Source: Indo Pos Online [in Indonesian, machine translated, edited]
<http://www.indopos.co.id/index.php?act=detail_radar&id=213740&c=94>


The number of dengue fever patients has grown to 387 people. Although
the rainfall has decreased, in April and in May as the peak of the
endemic spread [of] dengue hemorrhagic fever (DHF), [people] still
must be on extra alert.

Although several territories have done fogging or fumigation, the
situation for numbers of [dengue] patients continues to be quite
high. During the past April [2008], at least 387 dengue patients were
treated. This figure does not yet include the daily data of the
[dengue] patients for May, although to date in mid-May [2008], an
additional 96 [dengue] patients have been treated.

--
