******
[3] Brazil (Ceara)
Date: Fri 16 May 2008
Source: Estadao [in Portuguese, trans. & summ. Mod.TY, edited]
<http://www.estadao.com.br:80/vidae/not_vid174001,0.htm>


The state of Ceara now has 17 384 cases of dengue confirmed this year
[2008]. Most [of the cases] -- 10 381 cases (73.7 percent) -- have
been recorded in Fortaleza. The capital of Ceara also has 4 of the 9
deaths caused by this disease in the state. The other deaths occurred
in Caucaia, Redemption, Oros, Itapipoca, and Quixada, one in each of
these cities.

Another 20 deaths suspected to have been caused by the _Aedes
aegypti_ mosquito dengue vector are still under investigation,
according to the weekly newsletter released this Fri 16 [May 2008],
by the secretary of Health of Ceara.

The secretary of health of Fortaleza, Odorico Monteiro, now admits
that there is an epidemic in the city. Until last month [April 2008],
he spoke of a pre-epidemic of the disease, but the trend [in numbers
of dengue cases] has been increasing, with a shift in the epidemic curve.

In 2006, the highest concentration [of dengue cases] was in the month
of July with 4000 [dengue] patients. Last year [2007] there were 2000
cases in May and 3000 in April. After almost a month [this year,
2008], the secretary of health of the state of Ceara, Joao Ananias,
acknowledged that the state is facing an epidemic of dengue
hemorrhagic fever (DHF).

[Several collective mobilizations] to control and prevent dengue will
hit the streets of Fortaleza on Sat 17 [May 2008]. The work is being
done by the Prefecture of Fortaleza. The effort to eliminate the
breeding [sites] of the mosquito vector of the disease [virus] will
mobilize the participation of the population and various sectors of
the government.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-PORT
<promed@promedmail.org>

******
[4] Brazil (Sao Paulo)
Date: Fri 16 May 2008
Source: O Globo Online, Emissoras Pioneiras de Televisao (EPTV)
report [in Portuguese, trans. & summ. Mod.TY, edited]
<http://oglobo.globo.com/sp/mat/2008/05/16/casos_de_dengue_em_araraquara_chegam_1_043-427423722.asp>


Araraquara, 270 kilometers [168 miles] from the [state] capital,
registered 41 more dengue cases in a week. The total for the city for
the period 1 Jan [2008] until the present, reported this Friday [16
May 2008], was 1043 dengue cases, with 5 of these being imported
[from other localities]. Another 141 await [laboratory] test results.

The municipality is the 1st in Sao Paulo state to register an
epidemic of the disease, but according to Epidemiological
Surveillance the numbers [of dengue cases] is beginning to fall.
Colder weather is an ally in the control of the disease, because the
mosquito [dengue virus vector] _Aedes aegypti_ takes longer to reproduce.

At the peak of the epidemic, the municipality registered 123 cases in one week.

--
