******
[5] Brazil (Rio de Janeiro)
Date: Wed 14 May 2008
Source: Agencia Brasil [in Portuguese, trans. & summ. Mod.TY, edited]
<http://www.agenciabrasil.gov.br/noticias/2008/05/14/materia.2008-05-14.1808522097/view>


The Municipal Secretariat of Health reported today [14 May 2008] that
dengue virus has infected more than 80 400 people in the city this
year [2008]. Yesterday [13 May 2008] an additional dengue death due
to DHF was confirmed in the municipality. With this death, the number
of confirmed [dengue] deaths in Rio's capital reached 65,
[representing] more than half the total of 106 deaths in the entire
state according to the latest figures revealed the past week.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-PORT
<promed@promedmail.org>

[Globo (<http://g1.globo.com/Noticias/Rio/0,,MUL472412-5606,00
RIO+REGISTRA+MORTE+POR+DENGUE.html>, in Portuguese) reported an
additional dengue death in the city, for a total of 66, as well as
109 deaths in the state, 80 404 total dengue cases in the city, and
145 350 notified cases in the state.

